    grammar: { title: `Le style indirect : rapporter ce que quelqu'un a dit`, content: `Pour rapporter les paroles de quelqu'un, on utilise le discours indirect.

Ces changements s'opГЁrent :
вЂў am/is в†’ was
вЂў are в†’ were  
вЂў will в†’ would
вЂў can в†’ could

Exemples :
Direct : 'I'll call you back.' (Je te rappelle.)
Indirect : She said she would call me back.

Direct : 'I can't hear you.'
Indirect : He said he couldn't hear me.

Direct : 'Are you free tonight?'
Indirect : She asked if I was free that night.

Mots clГ©s : he said, she told me, they asked, I heard that...` },
