    grammar: { title: `Look forward to + -ing et autres verbes avec prepositions`, content: `'Look forward to' est suivi d un NOM ou d un VERBE en -ing, jamais d un infinitif :

CORRECT : I'm looking forward to the trip.
CORRECT : I'm looking forward to seeing you.
FAUX : I'm looking forward to see you.

Autres verbes qui prennent TOUJOURS -ing apres une preposition :
- keep on + -ing : Keep on trying.
- be used to + -ing : I'm used to waking up early.
- get used to + -ing : I'm getting used to driving.

Regle cle :
Apres une preposition (to, of, about, at...) on met TOUJOURS -ing.
I'm good at cooking.
I'm tired of waiting.
She's afraid of flying.` },
